description.plain:
Singer-songwriter Clinton Kane (b. November 26, 1998) is a Philippines native from Perth, Australia, who got his start off of YouTube. Specifically two of his original songs “this is what a toxic relationship feels like” and “this is what having a massive crush on someone feels like.” This sporadic beginning of a series ended up being the focus of his debut EP this is what it feels like, which features five live re-recordings of the aforementioned songs.

2020 proved to be a promising year for Clinton, as a collaboration with DJ Martin Garrix titled “Drown” was released on February 27, which garnered over +100 million streams on streaming services, as well as “i don’t want to watch the world end” being yet another example of the Australia native’s ability to convey emotion into 3 minutes.

Following the successful year, Clinton released the highly anticipated “CHICKEN TENDIES,” which amassed to become his first song to enter the Billboard Hot 100 chart, landing at #88.

songs.title: ​CHICKEN TENDIES

description.plain:
“CHICKEN TENDIES” is Clinton’s first single in 2021, following up the release of the November 2020 single “remember the mornings.” In the song, Clinton opens up about his shattered relationship with his mother, of which he lost to her strong devotion to God.

The song was first teased as a “lil idea” in October 20, 2020 on his TikTok, then was followed with another preview of the chorus in a stripped down format 2 weeks after.

On December 10, 2020, Clinton shared a snippet of the song with the caption: “haven’t leaked a song in forever so here we are.” Ironically, he leaked the entire song on an Instagram livestream just weeks before its release.

After 4 months of continuously building up the song’s release, the long-awaited fan favorite was finally slated for a February release,
